==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Understand
<hw>Un`der*stand"</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n`d⟦etil⟧r*st⟦acr⟧nd")</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Understood</conjf>
<pr>(⟦ucr⟧n`d⟦etil⟧r*st⟦oocr⟧d")</pr>, and <mark>Archaic</mark>
<conjf>Understanded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Understanding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>understanden</ets>, AS. <ets>understandan</ets>, literally, to
stand under; cf. AS. for<ets>standan</ets> to understand, G.
ver<ets>stehen</ets>. The development of sense is not clear. See
<er>Under</er>, and <er>Stand</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To have just
and adequate ideas of; to apprehended the meaning or intention of; to
have knowledge of; to comprehend; to know; <as>as, to
<ex>understand</ex> a problem in Euclid; to <ex>understand</ex> a
proposition or a declaration; the court <ex>understands</ex> the
advocate or his argument; to <ex>understand</ex> the sacred oracles; to
<ex>understand</ex> a nod or a wink.</as></def> <-- in ety, sic:
"development of sense"?? perh. s.b. "development of this sense"??
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Speaketh [<it>i. e.</it>, speak thou] so plain at this time, I you
pray,⟦br⟧
That we may <qex>understande</qex> what ye say.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>understand</qex> not what you mean by this.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Understood</qex> not all was but a show.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A tongue not <qex>understanded</qex> of the people.</q>
<rj><qau>Bk. of Com. Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be apprised, or have information, of; to learn;
to be informed of; to hear; <as>as, I <ex>understand</ex> that Congress
has passed the bill</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To recognize or hold as being or signifying; to
suppose to mean; to interpret; to explain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The most learned interpreters <qex>understood</qex> the words of
sin, and not of Abel.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To mean without expressing; to imply tacitly; to
take for granted; to assume.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>War, then, war,⟦br⟧
Open or <qex>understood</qex>, must be resolved.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To stand under; to support.</def> <mark>[Jocose &
R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To give one to understand</b></col>, <cd>to cause one to
know.</cd> -- <col><b>To make one's self understood</b></col>, <cd>to
make one's meaning clear.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Understand</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Understand
<hw>Un`der*stand"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To have the
use of the intellectual faculties; to be an intelligent being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Imparadised in you, in whom alone⟦br⟧
I <qex>understand</qex>, and grow, and see.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be informed; to have or receive
knowledge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I came to Jerusalem, and <qex>understood</qex> of the evil that
Eliashib did for Tobiah.</q> <rj><qau>Neh. xiii. 7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Understandable</ent>⟦br⟧
